text:
Meh. The positives of this review are limited: every employee I came into contact with was friendly and helpful, and the selection of items like carabineers, outdoor gear, and survival tools is better than average. And so ends the positives of this review.



The reality:

) Men's apparel sizes are limited to S, M, L, and maybe once in a while XL. I require XXL, and I found two items of apparel that actually fit me: 1) a stupid madras-flannel made in India button down shirt that looked hideous 2) a pullover sweatshirt that was almost too small for being an XXL. Cargo pants were idiotic in their manufacture, resembling lingerie in texture as the material used was almost nylon-tent instead of cotton, and with virtually no breathing room in the crotch and skin-tight calves. Again, mostly sizes for young boys, not real men. Prices were outrageously high, even for the simplest t-shirts (of which there were no t-shirts in my size).

) A $20 loyalty card program where you pay $20 and get $20 off your purchase and probably discounts thereafter. Really? Yeah, um, for me not so much.

) This store is conveniently located next to parking and restaurants but nowhere near tourist-populated areas. So, if you are local, have a  (lot) of money to spend and don't need anything above a Large and have a waist size under 32, you'll really enjoy shopping here! Fail.

I have trusted Yelp a lot so tried. 
Really?? I could not think this place is great;;
Nothing special.  Not many toppings;;
Also, I do not like their 'Tip-pushing' card reader.
It was very unpleasant  experience to be asked pay tips before I get my food.
I will not go there again.
